commit.message:
Change minimum Python from 3.5 to 3.6

I generally match support with the earliest Ubuntu LTS with mainline
support, and xenial (16.04, Python 3.5) drops support in April, with
the next earliest being bionic (18.04, Python 3.6).

Dropping 3.5 has the added benefit of removing tox workaround
conditions.
